				<div class="col-md-5" >
					<img src="images/portrait.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block" alt="Chef Marquise" >
					<h1>The Chef</h1>
					<p>Chef Marquise Vilmont was brought up in Haiti and Martinique.  She grew up loving to cook.  Since coming to Vancouver in 2009, her restaurant and catering has been making the locals rave about her sumptuous Caribbean Cuisine.</p>	
			</div>

				<div class="col-md-7">
								<h1 class="text-uppercase">A Word from Chef Vilmont</h1>
			<i>When people think of Caribbean they think of sunshine, vacation and fun. It is also known for very tasty and healthy cuisine.  But what makes our cuisine so different?​<br/>​<br/>
						
			The Caribbean cuisine is delicious because we have our own way to use and blend spices when we marinate the meat and when we cook. ​<br/>​<br/>
						
			We clean our meat with lemon, lime, sour oranges juices, vinegar before preparation. Then the meat is rinsed.​<br/>​<br/>
						
			Caribbean cuisine is very healthy.  We marinate all our meat making it easy to digest and use lots of fresh veggies and fresh fruits.​<br/> 
			This way we keep ourselves and our customers healthy....and happy.
			​<br/><br/>
			This is why Caribbean cuisine is so different, tasty and healthy. 
			When you taste it you know it's Caribbean cuisine.
			​<br/>
			To taste it is to love it!
			​<br/>
			We look forward to serve you!
			</i>		
			</div>
